main event: An unidentified flying object was observed over Chicago, Illinois on multiple occasions in 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as circular, larger than a baseball, and emitting a yellowish-green glow like a fluorescent street light.
The objects displayed unusual flight characteristics, such as a stationary outer circle with an inner circle spinning clockwise.
Some witnesses reported the objects made no sound and disappeared rapidly from view.
Multiple civilian and military witnesses reported seeing the objects, which were observed for time periods ranging from 30 seconds to 15 minutes.
The Air Force concluded the sightings were likely due to common aerial phenomena, but the witnesses stated the objects did not fit that explanation.
photographs: no photographs included in the reports
